# GitNexus Workflow

Use GitNexus MCP (Home `~/.cursor/mcp.json`) instead of blind repo-wide greps when exploring or changing code.

## Always do

- Before editing any symbol: `impact({target: "SymbolName", direction: "upstream"})` — report blast radius.
- When exploring: `query({query: "concept"})` instead of wide grep.
- For symbol context: `context({name: "SymbolName"})`.
- Before commit: `detect_changes()` (or `detect_changes({scope: "compare", base_ref: "main"})` for PR review).

## Never do

- Edit without prior `impact()` on the target symbol.
- Ignore HIGH or CRITICAL risk from impact analysis.
- Rename with find-and-replace — use GitNexus `rename`.
- Commit without running `detect_changes()`.

## Index maintenance

If `gitnexus status` reports stale: `.\scripts\gitnexus\Refresh-Index.ps1`

Skills: `.codex/skills/gitnexus-exploring/SKILL.md`, `gitnexus-impact-analysis`, `gitnexus-refactoring`.
